<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
  <!--
    Key Party is a Developer ID (non-sandboxed) app that hosts a WKWebView.

    WKWebView runs its JavaScript out-of-process in the system WebKit content
    process (com.apple.WebKit.WebContent), which is Apple-signed and does NOT
    inherit these entitlements — so, unlike Electron/CEF, the host needs no
    `com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit` or unsigned-executable-memory entitlement.

    The kiosk keyboard lock uses a CGEventTap gated by the runtime Accessibility
    (TCC) grant the user toggles in System Settings — a runtime permission, not a
    signing entitlement — so nothing is required for it here either.

    Intentionally empty. The codesign step in .github/workflows/release.yml signs
    with --options runtime (Hardened Runtime, required for notarization) using
    this file; add an entitlement below only if a future capability needs one.
  -->
</dict>
</plist>
